Former SABC COO Hlaudi Motsoeneng is scheduled to testify before the state capture inquiry on Tuesday. Editor's note: Livestream courtesy DStv 403, you can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - Former SABC COO Hlaudi Motsoeneng is scheduled to testify before the state capture inquiry on Tuesday. On Monday, former SABC Board chair Ben Ngubane told the inquiry that Motsoeneng was the right person for the job. Ngubane also said Motsoeneng not having a Matric certificate was never an issue. READ: Ex-SABC CEO describes Gupta mansion visit In 2014, the then Public Protector Thuli Madonsela found Motsoeneng's appointment irregular. The commission will also hear testimony from Anton Van Vuuren.